BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:10-1@thefinancelab.co
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20250902
SUMMARY:🎓 Sophomore grades count too
DESCRIPTION:Keep building the GPA and good habits. Colleges look at all four years.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:10-2@thefinancelab.co
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20251001
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20251002
SUMMARY:📚 Take the PSAT
DESCRIPTION:Many schools offer the PSAT in October. It is low-stakes practice and a useful baseline. Ask the counselor.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:10-3@thefinancelab.co
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20251015
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20251016
SUMMARY:💬 Explore careers and majors
DESCRIPTION:Talk about what your student is curious about. The app shows what majors can lead where.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:10-4@thefinancelab.co
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20251101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20251102
SUMMARY:🎓 Visit a campus
DESCRIPTION:Even a local college visit makes college feel real. Walk around, grab lunch, ask questions.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:10-5@thefinancelab.co
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260115
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260116
SUMMARY:💰 Run a net price calculator
DESCRIPTION:Pick a dream school and run its net price calculator together. The real number is often far below the sticker price.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:10-6@thefinancelab.co
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260215
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260216
SUMMARY:📅 Plan a balanced junior schedule
DESCRIPTION:Junior year is the big one. Help your student choose challenging but realistic courses.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:10-7@thefinancelab.co
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260501
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260502
SUMMARY:📚 Start an activity log
DESCRIPTION:Keep a running list of activities, roles, and accomplishments. It makes applications far easier later.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:10-8@thefinancelab.co
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
SUMMARY:📚 Make the summer count
DESCRIPTION:A job, internship, program, or volunteering builds skills and direction before junior year.
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
